President Muhammadu Buhari on Tuesday, commiserated with Minister of Communication and Digital Economy, Dr Isa Pantami, over the death of his daughter, Aisha. A statement signed by his spokesman, Garba Shehu, and made available to DAILY POST said that the president had earlier placed a call to the minister on Monday evening. It said that Buhari condoled with all members of the family on the sad event, urging comfort in the teachings of the Holy Prophet on the transient nature of life. President Buhari prayed that Allah will accept the soul of the departed, and grant her Jannah tul Firdaus, according to the brief statement.